780
01:13:24.740 --> 01:13:27.220
But in the beginning it was not so.

781
01:13:27.300 --> 01:13:30.463
A man may only divorce his wife
for unchastity.


782
01:13:30.540 --> 01:13:33.828
If he marries another, it is adultery.

783
01:13:34.580 --> 01:13:38.027
Some disciples said,
'If it is so for a man and his wife,


784
01:13:38.100 --> 01:13:40.182
it is best not to many.'

785
01:13:40.260 --> 01:13:44.231
He said to them, 'Only those
God appointed can accept this.'


786
01:13:45.260 --> 01:13:48.469
Some men are born eunuchs
from their mothers womb.


787
01:13:48.540 --> 01:13:51.430
Others were made so by men.

788
01:13:51.500 --> 01:13:55.266
Others became eunuchs
for the Kingdom of Heaven.


789
01:13:55.340 --> 01:13:57.547
Let those accept it who can."

790
01:13:59.740 --> 01:14:02.983
"Imitate me, as I imitate Christ.

791
01:14:03.060 --> 01:14:06.507
But know that Christ
is the head of all men,


792
01:14:06.580 --> 01:14:11.188
as a husband is the head of his wife,
and God the head of Christ.


793
01:14:11.260 --> 01:14:14.469
Any man who prays
with his head covered


794
01:14:14.540 --> 01:14:16.668
brings shame upon his head.

795
01:14:16.740 --> 01:14:20.461
Any woman who prays
with her head unveiled


796
01:14:20.540 --> 01:14:24.306
brings shame on her head,
as if it had been shaved.


797
01:14:24.380 --> 01:14:28.226
A woman who is unveiled,
is as if shorn.


798
01:14:28.300 --> 01:14:31.463
If it is shameful
for her to be shorn,


799
01:14:31.540 --> 01:14:33.190
she should wear a veil.

800
01:14:33.260 --> 01:14:35.308
A man must not cover his head,

801
01:14:35.380 --> 01:14:38.111
for he is the
image and glory of God,

802
01:14:38.180 --> 01:14:40.547
but woman is the glory of man.

803
01:14:40.620 --> 01:14:44.067
Man did not come from woman,
but woman from man.


804
01:14:44.660 --> 01:14:49.427
Man was not created for woman,
but woman for man.


805
01:14:49.500 --> 01:14:53.869
A woman must have
a sign of authority on her head,


806
01:14:53.940 --> 01:14:56.022
out of regard for the angels."

807
01:14:56.100 --> 01:14:58.910
Epistle of St Paul to the Corinthians.

808
01:16:00.220 --> 01:16:01.585
How the sea rises.

809
01:16:01.660 --> 01:16:05.665
The spring tide.
Monsieur de Marigny will have forgotten.


810
01:16:05.740 --> 01:16:09.187
If they are too tardy,
how will they get back?


811
01:16:09.260 --> 01:16:11.422
You're still not concerned?

812
01:16:11.500 --> 01:16:13.548
I hope they don't catch cold.

813
01:16:15.460 --> 01:16:17.667
Did you do as I did, Marquise?

814
01:16:17.740 --> 01:16:21.825
You wrote to someone?
I see a letter in your hands.


815
01:16:21.900 --> 01:16:24.267
To whom would I write, my dear?

816
01:16:24.340 --> 01:16:27.662
To Viscount de Prony, like you,
to admonish him.


817
01:16:27.740 --> 01:16:29.947
This letter you see

818
01:16:30.020 --> 01:16:32.068
is neither from me, nor to me.

819
01:16:32.140 --> 01:16:35.508
It's for Monsieur de Marigny,
and was just handed to me.


820
01:16:37.620 --> 01:16:40.544
- Is it from Paris?
- Yes, it is.


821
01:16:40.980 --> 01:16:42.982
You know this handwriting?

822
01:16:51.100 --> 01:16:55.105
Marquise, what an awful scribble.

823
01:16:55.180 --> 01:16:57.831
I know no one who writes like that.

824
01:17:00.140 --> 01:17:01.630
It's a woman's handwriting.

825
01:17:02.180 --> 01:17:03.420
A washer woman's.

826
01:17:03.500 --> 01:17:06.583
Washerwomen don't fold
their letters like this,


827
01:17:06.660 --> 01:17:09.630
or possess seals like this one. Look

828
01:17:13.140 --> 01:17:14.744
My God.

829
01:17:17.540 --> 01:17:19.781
Could it be that his old mistress,

830
01:17:19.860 --> 01:17:24.422
who has been silent until now,
has changed her mind?


831
01:17:24.500 --> 01:17:26.104
It would seem likely.

832
01:17:26.180 --> 01:17:30.265
She lay low for four months
and now springs back to life.


833
01:17:30.340 --> 01:17:31.990
Quite astute of her.

834
01:17:32.060 --> 01:17:33.824
She thinks by now

835
01:17:33.900 --> 01:17:36.790
the joy of a lovely young wife
has worn off.


836
01:17:37.580 --> 01:17:38.945
A big mistake.

837
01:17:39.020 --> 01:17:43.264
He's still deeply in love with his wife,
she's wasting her time.


838
01:17:43.340 --> 01:17:46.469
Coming from you,
this confidence reassures me.


839
01:17:46.540 --> 01:17:49.350
Yes, be reassured.

840
01:17:49.420 --> 01:17:53.220
Let's both be reassured.
What's a letter after all?


841
01:17:54.700 --> 01:17:56.623
There they are.

842
01:17:59.620 --> 01:18:02.590
We were caught by the tide.
We came back by boat.


843
01:18:02.660 --> 01:18:05.982
You're soaked.
Get warm by the fire.


844
01:18:06.060 --> 01:18:08.825
If you fall ill,
where will we be then.


845
01:18:09.580 --> 01:18:10.991
I'm not cold.

846
01:18:11.060 --> 01:18:13.028
I have to get used to the breeze,

847
01:18:13.100 --> 01:18:15.831
now I'm the wife of a man
who loves the sea.


848
01:18:15.900 --> 01:18:20.144
Monsieur de Marigny,
I was given a letter for you from Paris.


849
01:18:22.180 --> 01:18:23.341
Thank you.

850
01:19:19.420 --> 01:19:20.831
Why did you come here?

851
01:19:22.620 --> 01:19:25.146
Because it pleased me to.

852
01:19:25.220 --> 01:19:28.781
Isn't the open air
as much mine as anyone?


853
01:19:30.260 --> 01:19:32.262
I came here

854
01:19:33.500 --> 01:19:36.549
because I was bored
with not seeing you,


855
01:19:36.820 --> 01:19:39.869
because you didn't reply to my letters.

856
01:19:42.940 --> 01:19:45.386
Why did you pursue me here?

857
01:19:46.020 --> 01:19:49.342
If I feel like living on these shores,

858
01:19:49.420 --> 01:19:52.424
spending my days on this cliff...

859
01:19:52.500 --> 01:19:56.186
Doesn't it all belong to me
as much as to you?


860
01:19:56.260 --> 01:19:58.262
What are you afraid of?

861
01:20:00.220 --> 01:20:04.305
Deep down you're unsure of yourself.

862
01:20:06.060 --> 01:20:08.188
I like this place,

863
01:20:08.260 --> 01:20:10.308
and I want to live here.

864
01:20:12.380 --> 01:20:15.384
If I'm not wanted, go away.

865
01:20:16.140 --> 01:20:19.906
As for me,
I'm taking possession of it today.


866
01:20:24.420 --> 01:20:28.744
It could be said
that I came here like a beggar,


867
01:20:28.820 --> 01:20:32.461
to plead for a glance
from the sovereign,


868
01:20:33.180 --> 01:20:34.591
who...

869
01:20:35.620 --> 01:20:37.270
banished me...

870
01:20:44.340 --> 01:20:47.469
If I betrayed the love of my life,
I'd hate myself.


871
01:20:47.540 --> 01:20:49.622
So would you...

872
01:20:50.580 --> 01:20:52.787
If you refuse to put your arms

873
01:20:52.860 --> 01:20:55.431
for a minute around your Malaguena,

874
01:20:55.500 --> 01:20:57.502
you'd better kill me.

875
01:20:59.940 --> 01:21:02.591
At least then I'd feel no more pain.

876
01:21:02.660 --> 01:21:04.230
What are you waiting for?

877
01:21:05.020 --> 01:21:07.671
We're alone up here.

878
01:21:08.380 --> 01:21:10.269
See, there's no one.

879
01:21:10.340 --> 01:21:12.820
Take up your gun.

880
01:21:15.740 --> 01:21:17.071
You see...

881
01:21:18.780 --> 01:21:22.466
If anyone hears,
you missed a seagull.


882
01:21:24.980 --> 01:21:27.631
If I fall into the sea,

883
01:21:27.700 --> 01:21:31.022
you'll be sure to be faithful. Shoot.

884
01:21:33.660 --> 01:21:35.025
You're mad.

885
01:22:31.980 --> 01:22:33.425
Not now.

886
01:22:36.740 --> 01:22:38.310
She's asleep.

887
01:22:46.100 --> 01:22:47.511
Be good.

888
01:22:49.900 --> 01:22:51.390
One kiss.

889
01:22:52.780 --> 01:22:54.430
One kiss first.

890
01:22:56.180 --> 01:22:57.545
A real one.

891
01:23:16.060 --> 01:23:18.461
Weren't you going to
take the dogs out?


892
01:23:34.420 --> 01:23:36.184
Did Ryno wake you, Grandmother?

893
01:23:36.260 --> 01:23:40.868
No, my child, your husband
did not wake me. I wasn't asleep.


894
01:23:45.100 --> 01:23:47.068
Are you really leaving us?

895
01:23:47.140 --> 01:23:48.790
Winter is coming.

896
01:23:48.860 --> 01:23:51.466
Dampness doesn't agree with rheumatism.

897
01:23:53.620 --> 01:23:55.622
I love this place, 
I'm happy here.

898
01:23:55.700 --> 01:23:58.101
But I love you more than any place.

899
01:23:59.740 --> 01:24:02.471
If I ask him,
Ryno will return to Paris.


900
01:24:02.540 --> 01:24:04.304
Make sure you don't.

901
01:24:04.380 --> 01:24:06.348
You don't yet know, my sweet,

902
01:24:06.420 --> 01:24:08.787
how fragile is a woman's happiness.

903
01:24:08.860 --> 01:24:10.988
Ryno idolizes you.

904
01:24:11.060 --> 01:24:13.108
Here, what would he love,
if not you?


905
01:24:13.180 --> 01:24:14.750
But in Paris.

906
01:24:14.820 --> 01:24:16.629
There are so many distractions,

907
01:24:16.700 --> 01:24:21.467
and for a woman who is loved,
every distraction is a mortal enemy.


908
01:24:23.180 --> 01:24:25.387
You're right, Grandmother.

909
01:24:25.460 --> 01:24:29.067
No woman owns the key
to a man's heart for long.


910
01:24:29.660 --> 01:24:33.460
But if you miss us, send word,
and we'll return to Paris.


911
01:24:40.100 --> 01:24:44.185
There's no handsomer couple
in all Paris.


912
01:25:38.420 --> 01:25:39.910
Ryno.

913
01:25:42.100 --> 01:25:44.228
Not so fast.

914
01:26:08.060 --> 01:26:10.427
I didn't realize
you weren't following.


915
01:26:26.100 --> 01:26:27.704
I'm so silly.

916
01:26:41.020 --> 01:26:44.149
- Well, doctor?
- Madame de Marigny is pregnant.


917
01:26:57.660 --> 01:27:00.504
As of now,
I forbid you to get on a horse.


918
01:27:05.820 --> 01:27:07.265
Do you realize.

919
01:27:07.340 --> 01:27:09.707
When I think of it,
I break into a cold sweat...


920
01:27:20.860 --> 01:27:22.624
It's my son.

921
01:28:20.180 --> 01:28:22.308
Madame may catch cold.

922
01:28:22.900 --> 01:28:24.789
It is unwise in your state.

923
01:28:24.860 --> 01:28:26.624
It's lovely weather.

924
01:28:26.700 --> 01:28:28.668
I need fresh air.

925
01:28:46.500 --> 01:28:49.822
Keep covered,
the weather changes fast here.


926
01:28:50.460 --> 01:28:52.861
I'm a grown woman.

927
01:28:57.980 --> 01:29:01.701
Why, it's the lady of the manor,
the Marquise's daughter.


928
01:29:07.420 --> 01:29:08.910
Old Griffon.

929
01:29:11.180 --> 01:29:14.502
Who's that woman
sitting on a pile of ropes?


930
01:29:15.460 --> 01:29:17.110
You don't know her?

931
01:29:17.180 --> 01:29:19.148
Everyone around here knows her now.

932
01:29:20.620 --> 01:29:21.860
Often,

933
01:29:22.700 --> 01:29:24.748
she comes fishing with us.

934
01:31:14.020 --> 01:31:17.308
You're even handsomer
than when I first saw you.


935
01:31:18.300 --> 01:31:20.826
And now we're reunited.

936
01:31:20.900 --> 01:31:22.186
Be quiet.

937
01:32:14.900 --> 01:32:16.470
Talk, if you want...

938
01:32:18.860 --> 01:32:20.430
Say what you want.

939
01:32:22.540 --> 01:32:24.827
It's only too true that I came.

940
01:32:34.020 --> 01:32:35.988
As God is my witness,

941
01:32:37.180 --> 01:32:39.342
you're the cause of more kisses,

942
01:32:41.580 --> 01:32:43.264
of more tenderness for Hermangarde

943
01:32:43.340 --> 01:32:45.946
than I'd have given her
if you hadn't existed.


944
01:32:52.260 --> 01:32:54.228
I kissed her

945
01:32:55.860 --> 01:32:59.182
like a drowning man
clings to a floating log.


946
01:33:15.100 --> 01:33:17.182
They say that in battle,

947
01:33:18.620 --> 01:33:21.226
when thoroughbred horses
are lightly injured


948
01:33:21.300 --> 01:33:23.268
by a bayonet.

949
01:33:27.500 --> 01:33:30.185
A mysterious attraction for pain

950
01:33:31.420 --> 01:33:34.105
urges them forward
to impale themselves


951
01:33:34.980 --> 01:33:37.506
right to the heart.

952
01:33:42.940 --> 01:33:45.022
It's the same with you,

953
01:33:46.580 --> 01:33:48.821
since the day I saw you again.

954
01:35:30.660 --> 01:35:32.230
Is that my horse?

955
01:35:32.780 --> 01:35:34.384
It's just the wind.

956
01:35:34.460 --> 01:35:36.861
Don't leave me.

957
01:35:36.940 --> 01:35:38.704
It's the wind.

958
01:36:06.100 --> 01:36:07.784
It's the wind.

959
01:36:11.100 --> 01:36:13.421
It can't be her.

960
01:36:47.140 --> 01:36:49.666
You see, there's no one.

961
01:36:49.740 --> 01:36:51.504
Come back inside.

962
01:41:03.700 --> 01:41:05.464
Rebuke me.

963
01:41:14.380 --> 01:41:16.667
Tell me what you're thinking.

964
01:41:23.700 --> 01:41:25.828
You're worrying for nothing.

965
01:41:26.300 --> 01:41:28.268
Everything is fine.

966
01:41:49.380 --> 01:41:51.587
The worst is this silence.

967
01:42:07.940 --> 01:42:09.783
In fact, no.

968
01:42:09.860 --> 01:42:11.828
I was thinking of
Countess de Mendoze.


969
01:42:15.180 --> 01:42:17.148
You knew she died?

970
01:42:25.220 --> 01:42:27.541
Is she happier where she is now?

971
01:42:32.700 --> 01:42:35.271
You mean I kill everyone close to me.

972
01:42:36.820 --> 01:42:38.982
I didn't say that.

973
01:42:51.060 --> 01:42:53.540
There's something terrible in my fate.

974
01:42:54.580 --> 01:42:56.344
I always knew it.

975
01:43:16.100 --> 01:43:20.469
After a year and a half of uncertainty,
I have just now


976
01:43:20.540 --> 01:43:22.861
received the proof of something

977
01:43:22.940 --> 01:43:26.547
I had calculated and foreseen,

978
01:43:26.620 --> 01:43:29.430
as one calculates an eclipse.

979
01:43:29.500 --> 01:43:32.424
In fact, it is also an eclipse.

980
01:43:32.500 --> 01:43:36.630
That paragon of husbands,
Monsieur de Marigny...


981
01:43:36.700 --> 01:43:38.270
Monsieur de Marigny?

982
01:43:38.340 --> 01:43:40.342
...Has done like the dog in the Bible.

983
01:43:40.420 --> 01:43:43.663
He has returned...
you know where?


984
01:43:44.820 --> 01:43:47.221
What you're saying is most unsavory.

985
01:43:47.300 --> 01:43:48.950
Saying isn't doing.

986
01:43:49.020 --> 01:43:52.820
Let's see...
It's ten o'clock exactly.


987
01:43:52.900 --> 01:43:56.746
Where do you think
Monsieur de Marigny is now?


988
01:43:58.100 --> 01:44:01.707
That genius of conjugal love.

989
01:44:01.780 --> 01:44:03.191
My God.

990
01:44:04.260 --> 01:44:08.390
So my poor friend the Marquise de Flers
did well to die.


991
01:44:08.460 --> 01:44:13.068
He's at 46 rue des Cannes,

992
01:44:13.140 --> 01:44:14.790
at Senora Vellini's.

993
01:44:14.860 --> 01:44:16.510
Are you sure of this?

994
01:44:16.580 --> 01:44:20.027
He was at the opera last night
with his wife.


995
01:44:20.100 --> 01:44:23.547
He left around the same time I did...

996
01:44:23.620 --> 01:44:27.022
I saw him get into his carriage
under the arches.


997
01:44:27.100 --> 01:44:29.421
It was after Act Two.

998
01:44:29.500 --> 01:44:32.185
He left Madame de Marigny in her box,

999
01:44:32.260 --> 01:44:35.742
with Madame de Spaur
and Madame de Vanvres.


1000
01:44:35.820 --> 01:44:38.585
What proves he went to Rue de Cannes?

1001
01:44:38.660 --> 01:44:40.867
I saw him enter her house myself.

1002
01:44:41.940 --> 01:44:45.911
His carriage parked in front of the door

1003
01:44:45.980 --> 01:44:50.508
testified to the fact
to anyone who passed by.


1004
01:44:51.860 --> 01:44:53.225
Monsieur de Marigny

1005
01:44:53.300 --> 01:44:56.270
does not like secrecy.

1006
01:44:58.340 --> 01:45:00.581
What I like about him is that,

1007
01:45:00.660 --> 01:45:02.708
if one day he's a government minister,

1008
01:45:02.780 --> 01:45:06.182
he'll revel in being unpopular.

1009
01:45:07.180 --> 01:45:09.228
I know of no man who defies

1010
01:45:09.300 --> 01:45:11.064
opinion better than he.

1011
01:45:11.140 --> 01:45:12.710
Just like a man.

1012
01:45:13.460 --> 01:45:17.067
And You needn't believe me,
Monsieur de Prony,


1013
01:45:17.700 --> 01:45:21.341
but I swear he was madly in love
with Hermangarde.


1014
01:45:22.260 --> 01:45:25.787
I witnessed that love,
and I'll never forget it.


1015
01:45:25.860 --> 01:45:28.431
That's just as well, Countess.

1016
01:45:28.500 --> 01:45:30.662
That way,
at least someone will remember.


1017
01:45:31.420 --> 01:45:35.470
For he probably no longer does.